description:
Autism Awareness

Did you know? 

Autism now affects 1 in 88 children and 1 in 54 boys? Autism prevalence figures are growing, it is the fastest-growing serious developmental disability in the U.S. Autism also costs a family about $60,000 a year on average per child. Of that, Autism receives less than 5% of the research funding of many less prevalent childhood diseases. Boys are nearly five times more likely than girls to have autism.There is no medical detection or cure for autism. Know the signs, support the cause. Visit Austismspeaks.org for more info.
